  <![endif]-->
</head>

<body id="page-top" class="index">
  <!-- Navigation -->
  <nav class="navbar navbar-default navbar-fixed-top">
    <div class="container">
      <!-- Brand and toggle get grouped together for better mobile display -->
      <div class="navbar-header page-scroll">
          <button type="button" class="navbar-toggle" data-toggle="collapse" data-target="#bs-example-navbar-collapse-1">
            <span class="sr-only">Toggle navigation</span>
            <span class="icon-bar"></span>
            <span class="icon-bar"></span>
            <span class="icon-bar"></span>
        </button>
      </div>

      <div class="collapse navbar-collapse" id="bs-example-navbar-collapse-1">
        <ul class="nav navbar-nav navbar-right">
          <li>
            <%= link_to "Blog", "/blog", class: "color1" %>
          </li>
          <% %w(books articles speaking code).each_with_index do |section, i| %>
            <% content_tag :li do %>
              <%= link_to section.capitalize, "##{section}", class: "page-scroll color#{i+2}" %>
            <% end %>
          <% end %>
        </ul>
      </div> <!-- /.navbar-collapse -->
    </div> <!-- /.container -->
  </nav>

  <!-- Rainbow Bar -->
  <div class="top-bar"></div>

  <!-- Header -->
  <header id="top">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="row">
        <div class="col-md-12 text-center">
          <h2 class="greeting color4">Ohai! I'm</h2>
          <h1 class="color2">Benjamin Tan</h1>
          <h2 class="subheader">Software Engineer / Author / Speaker</h2>
          <ul class="list-inline social-btns">
            <li><a href="mailto:benjamintanweihao@gmail.com"><i class="fa fa-envelope-o color1"></i></a></li>
            <li><a href="https://twitter.com/bentanweihao" target=_blank><i class="fa fa-twitter color2"></i></a></li>
            <li><a href="#books" class="page-scroll"><i class="fa fa-angle-double-down color3"></i></a></li>
            <li><a href="https://sg.linkedin.com/in/benjamintanwh" target=_blank><i class="fa fa-linkedin color4"></i></a></li>
            <li><a href="http://github.com/benjamintanweihao" target=_blank><i class="fa fa-github color5"></i></a></li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="spacing"></div>
    </div>
  </header>

  <!-- Books -->
  <section id="books">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="spacing"></div>
      <div class="row">
        <div class="col-md-6 text-center">
          <div class="book">
            <img src="../images/writing/exotpbook.jpg"/>
          </div>
          <br/>
          <a href="http://www.manning.com/tanweihao?a_aid=exotpbook&a_bid=99f537ec" class="btn" target=_blank><i class="fa fa-2x fa-flask"></i> Go To Book Site</a>
        </div>  

        <div class="col-md-6">
          <h2 class="text-center">The Little Elixir & OTP Guidebook</h2>

            <p><strong>Note:</strong> This early access for the book is out on sale at
            <a href="http://www.manning.com/tanweihao?a_aid=exotpbook&a_bid=99f537ec" target=_blank>Manning Publications</a>!</p>

            <p>
              In this guidebook, I will show you how to build programs using <a href="http://www.elixir-lang.org" target=_blank>Elixir</a> and OTP. 
            </p>

            <p>
              Been meaning to do something useful with functional programming or simply itching for a fun weekend side-project? This book might be just for you. Come rediscover the joy of programming and what it feels like to be a beginner again.
            </p>

            <p>Grab your <a href="http://www.manning.com/tanweihao?a_aid=exotpbook&a_bid=99f537ec" target=_blank>copy</a> today and use <strong>mltanweihao</strong> for 50% off!</p>
        </div>  
      </div>
      <div class="spacing"></div>
    </div>

    <div class="container">
      <div class="spacing"></div>
      <div class="row">
        <div class="col-md-6 text-center">
          <div class="book">
            <img src="../images/writing/rubyclosures.png"/>
          </div>
          <br/>
          <a href="https://leanpub.com/therubyclosuresbook" class="btn" target=_blank><i class="fa fa-2x leanpub"></i> Go To Book Site</a>
        </div>  

        <div class="col-md-6">
          <h2 class="text-center">The Ruby Closures Book</h2>

          <p><strong>Get the book at <a href="https://leanpub.com/therubyclosuresbook" target=_blank>Leanpub</a> today!
          </p>

          <p>
            I have been a Ruby programmer for quite a number of years, but until recently, I have been blissfully ignorant of one of Ruby's most powerful features. That is, until one day, I saw a co-worker casually write a method that took in a block. Holy ****! I realized at that moment, I had a major gap in my Ruby knowledge.
          </p>

          <p>
            Sure, I knew how to use blocks, and vaguely knew how to use lambdas in Rails scopes. But who was I kidding? I was never going to be a competent Ruby programmer if I didn't fix this.
          </p>

          <p>
            Here's the thing. I spoke to a few of my Ruby programmer friends, and guess what, the situation is the same. If you are like that then this <a href="https://leanpub.com/therubyclosuresbook" target=_blank>book</a> is for you!
          </p>
        </div>  
      </div>
      <div class="spacing"></div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Articles -->
  <section id="articles">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="spacing"></div>
      <div class="row">

        <div class="col-md-12 text-center">
          <h2 >On Writing.</h2>
           <p>Some of the places where my writing has been featured:</p>
            <ul class="list-inline articles-btns">
              <li><a href="http://www.sitepoint.com/author/btan"><img src="../images/articles/sitepoint.png" alt="Sitepoint" class="img-responsive"></a></li>
              <li><a href="https://www.digitalocean.com/community/tutorials/how-to-optimize-unicorn-workers-in-a-ruby-on-rails-app"><img src="../images/articles/digitalocean.png" alt="" class="img-responsive"></a></li>
              <li><a href="http://blog.nitrous.io/2014/06/03/intro-to-elixir.html"><img src="../images/articles/nitrous.png" class="img-responsive" alt=""></a></li>
              <li><a href="http://www.neo.com/team/benjamin-tan"><img src="../images/articles/neo.svg" alt="" class="img-responsive"></a></li>
            </ul>
        </div>  
      </div>
      <div class="spacing"></div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Speaking -->
  <section id="speaking">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="spacing"></div>
      <div class="row">
        <div class="col-md-12 text-center">
          <h2 >On Speaking.</h2>
           <p>Conferences I have spoken at:</p>
            <ul class="list-inline speaking-btns">
              <li><a href="http://confreaks.com/videos/5078-RubyConf2014-rubyists-have-a-sip-of-elixir" target=_blank><img src="../images/speaking/rubyconf2014.png" alt="Sitepoint"></a></li>
              <li><a href="http://confreaks.com/videos/3845-rdrc2014-ruby-elixir-polyglotting-ftw" target=_blank><img src="../images/speaking/reddotrubyconf.png" alt=""></a></li>
              <li><a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=vS47DS3tn0k" target=_blank><img src="../images/speaking/geekcampsg.png" alt=""></a></li>
            </ul>
        </div>  
      </div>
      <div class="spacing"></div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Coding -->
  <section id="coding">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="spacing"></div>
      <div class="row">
        <div class="col-md-12 text-center">
          <h2 >On Coding.</h2>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="row">
        <div class="col-md-4 text-center">
          <h3>CodeRippa</h3>
          <p>Takes any source code (up to 150 languages) and turn it into a <em>beautiful</em> PDF.</p>
          <a href="http://code-rippa.heroku.com" target=_blank><img src="../images/coding/coderippa.png" alt=""></a>
        </div>

        <div class="col-md-4 text-center">
          <h3>Bookee|SG</h3>
          <p>Search for books in the National Library Board of Singapore easily.</p>
          <a href="https://play.google.com/store/apps/details?id=com.benjamintanweihao.bookeesg"><img src="../images/coding/bookeesg.png" alt=""></a>
        </div>

        <div class="col-md-4 text-center">
          <h3>Open Source Contributions</h3>
          <p>Projects that I've given back to:</p>
          <ul class="list-unstyled coding-btns">
            <li><a href="http://www.rubyonrails.org" target=_blank><img src="../images/coding/rails.png" alt="Ruby on Rails"></a></li>
            <li><a href="http://www.elixir-lang.org" target=_blank><img src="../images/coding/elixir.png" alt="Elixir"></a></li>
            <li><a href="https://spreecommerce.com/" target=_blank><img src="../images/coding/spree.png" alt="Spree Commerce"></a></li>
            <li><a href="https://github.com/phoenixframework" target=_blank><img src="../images/coding/phoenix.png" alt="Phoenix Framework"></a></li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div> 

      <div class="col-md-12 text-center">
        <a href="https://github.com/benjamintanweihao" class="btn" target=_blank><i class="fa fa-2x fa-github"></i>My Github Profile</a> 
      </div>
      <div class="spacing"></div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <%= partial "footer" %>
  <%= partial "javascripts" %>
</body>
</html>
